{"lemma":"أَعْزَلَ","slug":"أَعْزَلَ","root":"ع.ز.ل","root_slug":"ع-ز-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ز-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28995"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28995","headword_ar":"اَعْزَلُ","root":"Ezl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Sand ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramol","text_ar":"رَمْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from other sands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O.) ―         -b2-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having with him any weapon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzulN","text_ar":"عُزُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) occurring in a trad.; (O;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaAlN","text_ar":"مِعْزَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having with him a spear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K;) and the first is sometimes expl. as having this particular meaning: (TA:) pl. of the first, (S, O, K,) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzulN","text_ar":"عُزُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzolN","text_ar":"عُزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzolaAnN","text_ar":"عُزْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euz~alN","text_ar":"عُزَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) which is anomalous, but made to accord with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hus~arN","text_ar":"حُسَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAsirN","text_ar":"حَاسِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because nearly like it in meaning, (R, MF,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEozaAlN","text_ar":"اَعْزَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or or this is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzulN","text_ar":"عُزُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAziylu","text_ar":"مَعَازِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IJ, K,) which is anomalous, (TA,) and this is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaAlN","text_ar":"مِعْزَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) also. (K.) Hence, the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEozalu","text_ar":"الاَعْزَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simaAkaAni","text_ar":"سِمَاكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) i. e., to one of the two stars of which each is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imaAku","text_ar":"السِّمَاكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (TA;) because, unlike [the other"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smAk","text_ar":"سماك"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAmiHu","text_ar":"الرَّامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it has no star [near] before it that is regarded as its weapon; (S, * O, * K, * TA;) or because in the days of its rising [aurorally] there is no cold nor wind. (O, K.) ―         -b3-  And A bird"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that cannot fly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA.) ―         -b4-  And Clouds ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAb","text_ar":"سَحَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b5-  And A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his tail inclining to one side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not naturally."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazila","text_ar":"عَزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuw*u biA@ll~`hi mina AlA^aEozali EalaY AlA^aEozali","text_ar":"اَعُوذُ بِا@للّٰهِ مِنَ الاَعْزَلِ عَلَى الاَعْزَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek protection by God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man having with him no weapon, upon a"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horse of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Easiyb","text_ar":"عَسِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone of the tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the tail where the hair grows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is crooked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And [app. as an epithet applied to an ass or the like,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deficient in one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaroqafataAni","text_ar":"حَرْقَفَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which seems here to mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the crest of one of the two hip-bones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, O, K.) ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an absent man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K: *) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuzolN","text_ar":"عُزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, O.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","O","K","TA","S","R","MF","IJ","Mgh"]}]}}